<h3>How far is a light-year?</h3>
<p>Objects in our universe are extremely far away. In fact, they=E2=80=99re=
 so far away that kilometers or miles aren=E2=80=99t a useful measure of th=
eir distance. So, with this in mind, we speak of space objects in terms of =
<em>light-years</em>, the distance light travels in a year. Light is the fa=
stest-moving stuff in our universe. It travels at 186,000 miles per second =
(300,000 km/sec). So, a light-year is 5.88 trillion miles (9.46 trillion km=
). </p><div id=3D"cls-video-container-0YhVhxgV" class=3D"adthrive" style=3D=
