<p><a href=3D"https://earthsky.org/brightest-stars/sirius-the-brightest-sta=
r/" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">Sirius</a>: 8.6 miles (14 km)</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://earthsky.org/brightest-stars/vega-brilliant-blue-whit=
e-is-third-brightest-star/" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">Vega</a>: 25=
 miles (40 km)</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://earthsky.org/favorite-star-patterns/pleiades-star-clu=
ster-enjoys-worldwide-renown/" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">Pleiades<=
/a> open star cluster: 444 miles (715 km)</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://earthsky.org/brightest-stars/antares-rivals-mars-as-t=
he-scorpions-heart/" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">Antares</a>: 550 mi=
les (885 km)</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://earthsky.org/clusters-nebulae-galaxies/m13-finest-glo=
bular-cluster-in-northern-skies/" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">Hercul=
es globular star cluster</a> (aka M13): 25,000 miles (40,233 km)</p>
<p>Center of our <a href=3D"https://earthsky.org/astronomy-essentials/what-=
is-the-milky-way-galaxy/" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">Milky Way gala=
xy</a>: 26,100 miles (42,000 km)</p>
<p>Great <a href=3D"https://earthsky.org/clusters-nebulae-galaxies/andromed=
a-galaxy-closest-spiral-to-milky-way/" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">A=
ndromeda galaxy</a> (M31): 2,540,000 miles (4,087,000 km)</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sombrero_Galaxy" rel=3D"noopene=
r" target=3D"_blank">Sombrero galaxy</a> (M104): 28,000,000 miles (45,000,0=
00 km)</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2017/messier-51-the-whir=
lpool-galaxy" rel=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">Whirlpool galaxy</a> (M51)=
: 31,000,000 miles (50,000,000 km)</p>
<p>And so on, back to approximately 13 billion+ light-years to the farthest=
 galaxies: 13,000,000,000 miles (21,000,000,000 km)</p>
<p>Okay, the numbers are still pretty big! But hopefully they can help you =
see that our universe is very vast. And this video helps puts it in perspec=
tive.</p>
<p><iframe loading=3D"lazy" width=3D"708" height=3D"423" src=3D"cid:frame-7=
241ED04AADC37B7F6098925F48CE2A5@mhtml.blink" title=3D"Our Milky Way Galaxy:=
 How Big is Space?" frameborder=3D"0" allow=3D"accelerometer; autoplay; cli=
