their light years from Earth." width=3D"800" height=3D"587" class=3D"size-f=
ull wp-image-436985"><figcaption id=3D"caption-attachment-436985" class=3D"=
wp-caption-text">This chart shows objects close to home and takes us all th=
e way out to the Andromeda Galaxy, the most distant object most people can =
see with the unaided eye. And then, it shows one of the oldest galaxies eve=
r found. Image via <a href=3D"https://spaceplace.nasa.gov/light-year/en/" r=
el=3D"noopener" target=3D"_blank">NASA Space Place</a>.</figcaption></figur=
e>
<p>Bottom line: Here=E2=80=99s a way to understand the scale of light-years=
 in miles and kilometers.</p>
